1x01 Classroom Catastrophe

The life of 12-year-old Hank Zipzer, a young man with
a unique perspective on the world.

Ms Adolf gives the pupils an assignment to write an
essay about their summer holidays. Keen to avoid doing
any writing, Hank decides to build a model of his holiday
at Niagara Falls and demonstrate the experience to the
class instead. However, when he floods the classroom, Hank
lands himself in hot water. His punishment is to properly
write the essay and read it in front of the whole school
in assembly. Hank's friends rally to help but when Hank
stumbles at the eleventh hour in front of the whole
school, it's Mr Rock (Henry Winkler) who steps in.
